You never call `config()` anywhere. That would initialize `con`, so, without having called it, that is still `null`, and thus, `NullPointerException`.

Separately, catching an exception and just printing something is a really bad idea. If you can&#39;t handle them (and &#39;print something&#39; isn&#39;t handling them).

If the checked nature is a problem, rewrap them. Go into your IDE settings right now and fix the template - it needs to be:

```
try {
 .. code ..
} catch (CheckedException e) {
  throw new RuntimeException(&quot;unhandled&quot;, e);
}
```

_NOT_ `e.printStackTrace()` or `System.err.println(e)` or any other such &#39;print it and continue&#39; craziness.

